<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1305" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1305">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.77/124.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-17">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>It is impossible to do anything in the railway situation. The situation
                            has been further aggravated by the railway management’s refusal to give
                            the men service letters or transportation to the border. I have asked
                            Mr. Calero to express to the President this Embassy’s deep concern. I
                            will be glad to be instructed to take active steps to secure just
                            treatment for the men. Shall I sign a general certificate attesting the
                            service of these men and their reason for leaving the National Railways
                            service?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>